6 Section 1. R.S. 17:3399.12(5) and 3399.16(A), (B), and (C) are hereby amended and
7 reenacted to read as follows:
8 §3399.12. Definitions
9 As used in this Part, the following terms have the following meanings unless
10 the context clearly indicates otherwise:
11 * * *
12 (5) "Power-based violence" means any form of interpersonal violence
13 conduct intended to control, coerce, harm, exploit or intimidate another person on
14 the basis of sex through the assertion of power or authority over the person and
15 which shall include the following:
16 (a) Dating violence (R.S. 46:2151).
17 (b) Any conduct prohibited by R.S. 14:73.13 or 73.14, or any successor
18 statute, involving media generated by artificial intelligence or deepfake media
19 depicting sexual imagery.
20 (b)(c) Domestic abuse and family violence (R.S. 46:2121.1 and 2132). For
21 the purposes of this Part, domestic abuse shall also include any act or threat to act
22 that is intended to coerce, control, punish, intimidate, or exact revenge on the other
23 party, for the purpose of preventing the victim from reporting to law enforcement or
24 requesting medical assistance or emergency victim services, or for the purpose of
25 depriving the victim of the means or ability to resist the abuse or escape the
26 relationship.
