22 §3399.16. Safety education; recognition and reporting of potential threats to safety
23 A. Not later than the beginning of the fall semester of 2022 2026, the
24 administration of each institution, in consultation with campus or local law
25 enforcement agencies, shall develop and distribute, not less than four times per
26 academic year through in-person or online delivery or both, information to
27 students regarding power-based violence, campus safety, and internet and cell phone
28 safety and online content that is a potential threat to school safety.
29 B. The information shall include the following:
30 (1) Instruction on how to identify and the identification, prevent prevention,
